criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Diagnostic and Statistical Manual (DSM)-IV diagnosis of schizophrenia,
             schizoaffective disorder, schizophreniform disorder, delusional disorder or brief
             psychotic disorder;

          2. 26 to 64 years;

          3. illness duration <5 years;

          4. positive symptoms of mild or lower severity (rating <4 in all items of Positive
             Symptom Subscale of PANSS);

          5. impaired functioning with SOFAS score <=60;

          6. Cantonese speaking.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  substance abuse

          -  organic psychotic disorders and

          -  mental retardation
